snippet.textDisplay:
JaVale McGee was, is and always will be a ridiculous man. He isn't a bad player, but he blacks out sometimes and does - yes, he still does, even if his mom disagrees (come on, really? 30-something year old millionaire needs mommy to defend him?) - unbelivably dumb things on the court.
Is Shaq nasty sometimes, maybe even a bully? Yes, but honestly I prefered his old way to the constant ass-kissing that we see now. If on TNT they keep saying how incredible is Chriss Paul and how talented are players that score 30+ pts but shooting 20% from 3, I WILL puke... 😒😁
And btw I never understood the uncle tom argument, seems just a way to deflect. Granted, I'm a white man and I don't even live in the US, so maybe I'm missing something, but McGee does do stupid stuff. And Shaq is an NBA analyst, a black dominated sport. Most white players don't play enough to be on Shaqtin... 😂


PS: 2 rings? Come on, playing center with the 2-MVPs Warriors... even Zaza Pachulia has a ring. Before KD

snippet.textDisplay: Shaq is one of the most skill-less basketball players to play in the NBA.  This doesn't mean to say he wasn't a dominant big man.  He just couldn't shoot, pass or dribble the ball at an NBA level... pretty much all of the things other players need.  If Shaq was even 6'9 he probably would not have made the league - fortunately, he wasn't and some of us got to see him impose his will and jam balls on people for at least 16 out of his 19 years.  To boot - he was and still is one of the most entertaining personalities from the league.  I just find it interesting that he thinks he is one of the best basketball players of all time (implying he had skill and not just outrageous athleticism for a big man) as he isn't.  He is one of the most dominant players of all time though.
